6 SUMMARY
77 This bill expands from one to 3 the number of on-premises retail liquor licensees a
88 person or persons who hold a majority ownership interest in a manufacturing licensee may
99 hold no less than a majority ownership interest in. The on-premises retail locations may be
1100 at the manufacturing facility or other locations. If a person or persons hold a majority
1111 ownership interest in 2 or more manufacturing licensees that collectively manufacture at
1122 least 1,000 barrels per year, the person or persons may hold no less than a majority
1133 ownership interest in up to 6 on-premises retail licensees. The bill limits a person or
1144 persons who hold a majority ownership interest in one or more manufacturing licensees to
1155 holding an ownership interest in no more than 6 on-premises retail licensees. The bill also
1166 adds tenant breweries and tenant wineries to the provision of law requiring on-premises
1177 liquor sales to be charged sales tax at the rate of 8%.
